        public Pedigree(String fmUrlStr,
                boolean listNotCat,
                List excludeList)
        Constructs a new Pedigree object that will connect to the file manager at the given URL specified by the fmUrlStr string parameter.
        Parameters:
        fmUrlStr - The String URL of the file manager to connect to.
        listNotCat - Whether or not we should include non-cataloged products in the pedigree.
        excludeList - A List of String ProductType names that should be excluded from the Pedigree.

    • Method Detail

      • doPedigree

        public PedigreeTree doPedigree(Product orig,
                               boolean upstream)
        Performs a full pedigree of the specified Product orig . If upstream is set to true, an upstream pedigree is performed, otherwise, a downstream pedigree is performed.
        Parameters:
        orig - The Product to perform a pedigree of.
        upstream - Whether or not we should do an upstream (true) or downstream (false) pedigree.
        Returns:
        A PedigreeTree containing the Pedigree of a given product.

      • getUpstreamPedigreedProducts

        public List getUpstreamPedigreedProducts(Product orig)
        Returns the most direct ancestors (a List of Products) upstream from the given Product named orig.
        Parameters:
        orig - The Product to get direct upstream relatives of.
        Returns:
        A List of Products directly upstream from the given Product.

      • getDownstreamPedigreedProducts

      • getWorkflowInstProds

        public List getWorkflowInstProds(String wInstId)
        Gets all associated Products with the provided WorkflowInstance identified by its ID (the wInstId string parameter).
        Parameters:
        wInstId - The ID of the WorkflowInstance to look up the Products for.
        Returns:
        A List of Products associated with the provided Workflow Instance ID.
